{{News|April 20, 2017|Article descriptions and the 'See also' template|Your wiki admins have been experimenting by setting a [[Property:Article_description|Article description]] property in the body of some articles. The goal is to expose more data points and obtain an increasing amount of modularity across the site. Ultimately wiki contributors will eventually write less (and deduplicate) content by using templates to grep for data from other articles (such as the [[Template:See also|See also]] template). Properties come with [https://www.semantic-mediawiki.org Semantic MediaWiki], an extension to MediaWiki, and can be confusing, so be sure to read up them before getting too carried away.}}

